.TH "xenbus_map_ring_valloc" 9 "xenbus_map_ring_valloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xenbus_map_ring_valloc \- 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" xenbus_map_ring_valloc
.BI "(struct xenbus_device *dev "  ","
.BI "grant_ref_t *gnt_refs "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nr_grefs "  ","
.BI "void **vaddr "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
xenbus device
.IP "gnt_refs" 12
grant reference array
.IP "nr_grefs" 12
number of grant references
.IP "vaddr" 12
pointer to address to be filled out by mapping
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Map \fInr_grefs\fP pages of memory into this domain from another
domain's grant table.  xenbus_map_ring_valloc allocates \fInr_grefs\fP
pages of virtual address space, maps the pages to that address, and
sets *vaddr to that address.  Returns 0 on success, and -errno on
error. If an error is returned, device will switch to
XenbusStateClosing and the error message will be saved in XenStore.
